import "@a10n/blueprint-typespec";
import "../../../dependencies/github/main.tsp";
import "../../review-agent/main.tsp";
import "../models/main.tsp";
import "../../review-relational-store/main.tsp";

using State;
using Dependencies.Github;
using Components.ReviewAgent;
using Components.ReviewRelationalStore;

namespace Components.ReviewApiService.Flows.Recovery;

@flow
@dependsOn([Components.ReviewAgent])
@reads([StoredReview])
@writes([StoredReview])
@doc("""
On ReviewApiService process restart, in-flight {@Review} records are reconciled against live {@ReviewAgent} sessions to prevent silent failures and ensure no review is permanently stuck in {@ReviewStatus.pending} or {@ReviewStatus.running}.

On restart, ReviewApiService executes the following recovery sequence:

1. Query {@ReviewRelationalStore} for {@Review} records with {@Review.status} IN [{@ReviewStatus.pending}, {@ReviewStatus.running}].
2. For each {@ReviewStatus.running} {@Review}: query {@ReviewAgent} session history.
   - Active session: re-subscribe to {@StreamEvent} stream and resume broadcasting {@StreamEventType.STATE_DELTA} updates.
   - Completed session: apply {@ReviewResult} and transition {@Review.status} to {@ReviewStatus.completed}.
   - Session not found: transition {@Review.status} to {@ReviewStatus.failed} with reason `agent_session_lost`.
3. For each {@ReviewStatus.pending} {@Review} older than 30 seconds: re-dispatch {@ReviewInput} to {@ReviewAgent} (idempotent on duplicate {@Review.id}).

### Idempotency

GitHub may redeliver the same webhook (same X-GitHub-Delivery header). ReviewApiService deduplicates on {@ReviewWebhookEvent.review_id} before inserting a new {@Review} row. Duplicate deliveries return the existing {@Review.id} with 200 status.
""")
op recovery_flow(): void;
